text.0:
#COVID19 has shown what humanity is capable of at its best & worst:
Inspiring acts of compassion & self-sacrifice
Breathtaking feats of science & innovation
Heart-warming demonstrations of solidarity
But also disturbing signs of self-interest, blame-shifting & division
#UNGASS
text.1:
At #UNGASS on #COVID19, I called on world leaders to:
:keycap_1:invest in vaccines to end the pandemic
:keycap_2:invest in preparedness to prevent the next pandemic
:keycap_3:invest in health as the foundation of peace & prosperity
:keycap_4:invest in multilateralism to safeguard our common future
#ACTogether https://t.co/pe4eTJXMDk
text.2:
We must ALL come together as one big global family to beat COVID-19. I am proud to lend my voice (and my dance moves!) to the #WeAreFamily campaign with Kim Sledge, @The_WorldWeWant @thewhof in benefit of @WHO.

To learn more or sing with us, visit https://t.co/N4e6VDIR9I. https://t.co/PKDbp3rFvZ
text.3:
Happy International Day of Volunteers! 

Volunteers are more important now than ever. Thank you, volunteers, for your response to the #COVID19 crisis. But volunteer action is not enough. They need support.  They need us to #ACTogether, because #TogetherWeCan end this crisis! https://t.co/17yvtgAZ0C
text.4:
#WeAreFamily! We are proud to support the @WHO & @thewhof promoting unity in response to COVID-19.
